My experience here tonight was incredibly awful. I asked to order a Chicken Pizziola, which is technically no longer on the menu but they have all of the ingredients to make it and every Subway I've gone to for the last 6 years makes it for me and charges me for another sandwich that is the same price. This guy refused to make it and demanded that I order from the menu. He yelled at me, cursed at me, and refused my business. I left and went to Subway on 111 Broadway and they happily took my order and made the sandwich. It's unbelievable that a business would be so willing to lose a customer. I will never go here again, there are 4 other Subways right in the area and they'll get my business from now on, and I eat a lot of Subway, have been since 1996 :)

When in the area of the Staten Island Ferry, Battery Park City and The famous 'Wall Street Bull", you may need a bite to eat and escape the heat, and this Subway is the place to be.  The best time to have a great experience here is on the weekends, mostly Sunday's, you want a nice sandwich healthy eating, and still be in the mecca of all the fun things around.  It's not too hidden away, the staff is friendly, they may not speaking great english, but my experience was pretty awesome.  They even asking me about my GoPro camera strapped to my head as I was walking the area capturing awesome footage of the sights at Battery Park City.  I choose here over the BK and Chipotle near by based on the price, no crowds and healthy options.  Did I mention my sandwich was amazing, JAMMED PACK with Veggies and the Best tasting sandwich I ever created at a Subways.  My tab with barely over $7.25 via I bought a lemonade rather than their fountain drink.  Live Life Unscripted.

This place is a joke and shouldn't be allowed to operate under the Subway name.
